Company Description: Wendy's International Is A Chain Of Restaurants That Operates And Franchises More Than 6,500 Outlets IN The United States And IN 21 Other Countries, As Well As Territories. Based IN Bayonne, N.J., Its Menu Comprises An Array Of Food Items, Such As Garden Sensations Salads, Combo Choices, Super Value Menu, Frosty Shakes, Frosty Float And Boneless Chicken Wings, Among Others. The Company Is A Subsidiary Of Wendy's/Arby's Group Inc., One Of Largest Quick Service Restaurant Companies IN The United States.

Wendy's Is A Chain Of More Than 6,500 Hamburger Restaurants IN North America And Other International Markets. Founded IN 1969, The Chain S Restaurants Serve A Variety Of Hamburgers Made With Grilled Beef And Vegetable Toppings. Its Restaurants Also Serve Garden Salads, Grilled Chicken Sandwiches And Baked Potatoes. The Chain S Restaurants  Side Dishes Include French Fries, Chocolate Chip Cookies, Chicken Nuggets And Yogurt. Its Restaurants Also Offer Wendy S Kids  Meal. Wendy's Operates Bakeries That Supply Sandwich Buns. The Chain Additionally Participates IN Various Community Activities, Such As Animal Welfare Programs, Educational Plans And Foster Care Adoption Schemes. Wendy's Is Owned And Operated By Wendy S International.

Established IN 1969, Wendy's Is A Chain Of Fast-Food Restaurants Specializing IN Hamburgers. Located IN Bridgewater, N.J., It Offers A Range Of Combos, Hamburgers, Meals, Desserts And Hot/Cold Beverages. Some Of Its Flagship Products Include Old Fashioned Combos, Old Fashioned Hamburgers, Pair 2, Garden Sensations Salads, Wendy's Kids Meal, Frosty And More. Wendy's Is A Part Of The Wendy's/Arby's Group Inc., One Of The Largest Quick-Service Restaurant Companies IN The United States That Comprise The Wendy's And Arby's Brands.
